"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.3</span> Inn</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מָלוֹן, ארח</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(malon ’orchim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:1\">JER 9:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κατάλυμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kataluma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:7\">LUK 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir14:25\">SIR 14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc3:45\">1MA 3:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Odes1:13\">ODA 1:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">πανδοχεῖον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pandocheion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">πανδοχεύς</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pandocheus (“innkeeper”))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:35\">LUK 10:35</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ταβέρνη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tabernē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:15\">ACT 28:15</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The inn was a place for the lodging of travelers. Meals were also served. Unlike some modern bars and hotels, it did not have particular associations with alcohol or prostitution.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In some languages it may be necessary to describe the role of an inn as “a place where people could stay overnight and get something to eat” or even “a place where people could pay in order to stay overnight and get something to eat.” Compare <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ’s rendering of inn in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:1\">JER 9:1</a>, where it has “a house where travelers spend the night.” It is highly likely this is the only place in the Old Testament where the Hebrew word <em>malon</em> refers to an actual inn or permanent structure for the lodging of travelers.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
